{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b7222d0-ce01-43cb-a110-936abd707d4d","content":"The project doesn't exist yet at that path, but here's how to configure it. Create or edit `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — most C# MCP servers use stdio transport (the server reads/writes JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout).\n- **`command`/`args`** — uses `dotnet run` so you don't need to pre-build.\n- If you publish a self-contained binary instead, point `command` directly at the executable.\n- If your server uses **SSE/HTTP** transport instead, use `type: \"sse\"` with a `url` field instead of `command`/`args`.\n\nAfter saving, open the Copilot Chat panel in agent mode (`@workspace`) and it will discover the server's tools automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93394bbd-7b8e-4f2c-8ac5-c046bda0a44e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist at that path. That's fine — the user is asking how to configure mcp.json, not asking me to build the server. I can give them the configuration guidance directly.","outputTokens":330},"id":"e7123a4d-e2fc-46e1-bd08-f3761b8fa5d4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:04:41.355Z","parentId":"2f049ffb-dffb-429d-98ed-a4e3f24e29c5"}
